############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ ($r,$s) = num_sort(random_subset(2,2..12)); $a = -0.8; $b = 0.8*($s - $r); $c = 0.8*$r*$s; Context("Units")->withUnitsFor("time"); $answer = Compute("$s s");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML For a falling object on the Moon, with height measured in meters and time measured in seconds, the curvature coefficient of its height function is (roughly) [`-0.8\text{.}`]
An object on Mars is shot straight up from a height of [`[$c]`] meters with an initial speed of [`[$c]`] meters per second. How long will it take for the object to land?
[_]{$answer}{16}
END_PGML
